  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  children between the age of 5 years and 15 years with the diagnosis of recurrent acute
             sinusitis who are attending the outpatient pediatric department, pediatric allergy
             clinic, and the ear, nose, throat clinic.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients who have allergic rhinitis, chronic sinusitis, a history of allergic
             reactions to azithromycin or macrolides, treatments with immunotherapy or IVIG or
             gentamycin solution or pneumococcal vaccine during study period.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
